.TH WHISRS 1 "2026-03-14" "whisrs 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
whisrs \- Linux-first voice-to-text dictation CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B whisrs
.I subcommand
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B whisrs
is a thin CLI client that communicates with
.BR whisrsd (1)
over a Unix domain socket.
It sends commands (toggle, cancel, status) and prints the daemon's response.
.PP
The
.B setup
subcommand runs an interactive onboarding flow and does not require the daemon.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B setup
Interactive onboarding \(em select a transcription backend, enter an API key,
test the microphone, and write
.IR config.toml .
Does not require the daemon to be running.
.TP
.B toggle
Start or stop recording. If idle, begins audio capture. If recording,
stops capture and sends audio for transcription. Text is typed at the
cursor in the previously focused window.
.TP
.B cancel
Cancel the current recording and discard captured audio. Returns the
daemon to the idle state. Has no effect if the daemon is not recording.
.TP
.B status
Query the daemon state. Prints one of:
.BR idle ,
.BR recording ,
or
.BR transcribing .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B WHISRS_GROQ_API_KEY
Groq API key. Overrides the value in
.IR config.toml .
.TP
.B WHISRS_OPENAI_API_KEY
OpenAI API key. Overrides the value in
.IR config.toml .
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Directory for the Unix socket. The socket is created at
.IR $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/whisrs.sock .
Falls back to
.IR /tmp/whisrs\-<uid>.sock .
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Directory for configuration. Config file is read from
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/whisrs/config.toml .
Defaults to
.IR ~/.config/whisrs/config.toml .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/whisrs/config.toml
Main configuration file. Created by
.BR "whisrs setup" .
Contains backend selection, API keys, language, and audio settings.
Permissions should be 0600 since it may contain API keys.
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/whisrs.sock
Unix domain socket for CLI\-daemon IPC.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/whisrs/recovery/
Recovery directory for audio that failed transcription.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (daemon not running, invalid state transition, or setup failure).
.SH EXAMPLES
Run interactive setup:
.PP
.RS
.B whisrs setup
.RE
.PP
Start dictation (bind this to a hotkey):
.PP
.RS
.B whisrs toggle
.RE
.PP
Cancel recording:
.PP
.RS
.B whisrs cancel
.RE
.PP
Check daemon state:
.PP
.RS
.B whisrs status
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR whisrsd (1)
